obj_root_law_sections_1:
  sectionId (24097)
  sectionNo (1)
  orderNo 1
  title `Short title, extent and commencement.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_1_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24097&sectionno=1&orderno=1&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_1_content:
  string
  line `(1) This Act may be called the Delhi Urban Art`
  line `Commission Act, 1973.`
  line
  line `(2) It extends to the whole of the Union territory of Delhi.`
  line
  line `(3) It shall come into force on such date ^1`
  line `as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, appoint.`
obj_root_law_sections_1_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 1st May, 1974, vide notification No. G.S.R. 189(E), dated the 27th April, 1974, see Gazette of India, Extraordinary, Part II,`
  line `sec. 3(i).`
obj_root_law_sections_2:
  sectionId (24098)
  sectionNo (2)
  orderNo 2
  title Definitions.
  content obj_root_law_sections_2_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24098&sectionno=2&orderno=2&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_2_content:
  string
  line `In this Act, unless the context otherwise requires,--`
  line
  line `(a) "building" includes any structure or erection or part of a structure or erection which is`
  line `intended to be used for residential, industrial, commercial or other purposes, whether in actual use or`
  line not;
  line
  line `(b) "building operations" includes rebuilding operations, structural alterations of, or additions to,`
  line `buildings and other operations normally undertaken in connection with the construction of buildings;`
  line
  line `(c) "Commission" means the Delhi Urban Art Commission established under section 3;`
  line
  line `(d) "Delhi" means the Union territory of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(e) "development" with its grammatical variations means the carrying out of building,`
  line `engineering, mining or other operations in, on, over or under, land or the making of any material`
  line `change in any building or land and includes re-development;`
  line
  line `(f) "engineering operations" includes the formation or laying out of means of access to a road or`
  line `the laying out of means of water supply;`
  line
  line `(g) "local body" means the Delhi Municipal Corporation established under the Delhi Municipal`
  line `Corporation Act, 1957 (66 of 1957), the New Delhi Municipal Committee constituted under the`
  line `Punjab Municipal Act, 1911 (Punjab Act III of 1911), as in force in Delhi, the Delhi Development`
  line `Authority constituted under the Delhi Development Act, 1957 (61 of 1957), or any other local`
  line `authority concerned with urban development of Delhi;`
  line
  line `(h) "member" means a member of the Commission and includes its Chairman;`
  line
  line `(i) "public amenity" includes road, water supply, street lighting, drainage, sewerage, public works`
  line `and such other convenience as the Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `specify to be a public amenity for the purposes of this Act;`
  line
  line `(j) "regulation" means a regulation made under this Act by the Commission;`
  line
  line `(k) "rule" means a rule made under this Act by the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_2_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_3:
  sectionId (24099)
  sectionNo (3)
  orderNo 3
  title `Establishment of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_3_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24099&sectionno=3&orderno=3&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_3_content:
  string
  line `(1) With effect from such date as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint, there shall be established a Commission by the name`
  line `of the Delhi Urban Art Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall be a body corporate having perpetual succession and a common seal with`
  line `power to acquire, hold and dispose of property and to contract and shall by the said name sue or be sued.`
obj_root_law_sections_3_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_4:
  sectionId (24100)
  sectionNo (4)
  orderNo 4
  title `Composition of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_4_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24100&sectionno=4&orderno=4&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_4_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall consist of a Chairman and such`
  line `number of other members, being not less than two and not more than four as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, appoint from amongst persons who, in the opinion of the`
  line `Central Government, have sensibility and interest in the plastic and visual arts and urban environment, or`
  line `possess special knowledge or practical experience in respect of architecture or art.`
obj_root_law_sections_4_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_5:
  sectionId (24101)
  sectionNo (5)
  orderNo 5
  title `Terms and conditions of service of members.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_5_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24101&sectionno=5&orderno=5&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_5_content:
  string
  line `(1) A member shall, unless his appointment is`
  line `terminated earlier by the Central Government, hold office for a term of three years from the date of his`
  line appointment.
  line
  line `(2) A person who holds, or who has held, office as Chairman or member shall be eligible for`
  line `re-appointment to that office once, but only once.`
  line
  line `(3) A member may resign his office by writing under his hand addressed to the Central Government,`
  line `but he shall continue in office until his resignation is accepted by the Central Government.`
  line
  line `(4) A casual vacancy caused by the resignation of a member under sub-section (3) or for any other`
  line `reason, shall be filled by fresh appointment.`
  line
  line `(5) A member may be appointed either as a whole-time or part-time member as the Central`
  line `Government thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(6) Subject to the foregoing provisions, the terms and conditions of service of the Chairman and other`
  line `members shall be such as may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_5_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_6:
  sectionId (24102)
  sectionNo (6)
  orderNo 6
  title `Meetings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_6_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24102&sectionno=6&orderno=6&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_6_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall meet at such times and places and shall`
  line `observe such rules of procedure in regard to the transaction of business at its meetings as may be`
  line `prescribed by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_6_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_7:
  sectionId (24103)
  sectionNo (7)
  orderNo 7
  title `Vacancies amongst members or defect in constitution not to invalidate acts or proceedings of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_7_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24103&sectionno=7&orderno=7&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_7_content:
  string
  line `No act or proceeding of the Commission shall be deemed to be invaild by reason`
  line `merely of any vacancy in, or any defect in the constitution of, the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_7_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_8:
  sectionId (24104)
  sectionNo (8)
  orderNo 8
  title `Temporary association of persons with the Commission for particular purposes.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_8_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24104&sectionno=8&orderno=8&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_8_content:
  string
  line `(1) The`
  line `Commission may associate with itself, in such manner and for such purposes as may be determined by`
  line `regulations, any person whose assistance or advice it may desire in carrying out any of the provisions of`
  line `this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) A person associated with it by the Commission under sub-section (1) for any purpose shall have a`
  line `right to take part in the discussions relevant to that purpose, but shall not have a right to vote at a meeting`
  line `of the Commission, and shall not be a member for any other purpose.`
obj_root_law_sections_8_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_9:
  sectionId (24105)
  sectionNo (9)
  orderNo 9
  title `Appointment of staff of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_9_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24105&sectionno=9&orderno=9&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_9_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government shall, in consultation`
  line `with the Commission, appoint a Secretary of the Commission who shall hold office during the pleasure of`
  line `the Central Government:`
  line
  line `Provided that the first appointment of the Secretary may be made by the Central Government without`
  line `consultation with the Commission.`
  line
  line `(2) The terms and conditions of service of the Secretary shall be such as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Subject to any rules, the Commission may appoint such other employees as it may think necessary`
  line `for the efficient performance of its functions under this Act, and the terms and conditions of service of the`
  line `employees so appointed shall be such as may be determined by regulations.`
obj_root_law_sections_9_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_10:
  sectionId (24106)
  sectionNo (10)
  orderNo 10
  title `Authentication of orders and other instrument of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_10_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24106&sectionno=10&orderno=10&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_10_content:
  string
  line `All orders and decisions`
  line `and other instruments of the Commission shall be authenticated by the signature of the Secretary or any`
  line `other officer of the Commission duly authorised by it in this behalf.`
obj_root_law_sections_10_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_11:
  sectionId (24107)
  sectionNo (11)
  orderNo 11
  title `Functions of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_11_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24107&sectionno=11&orderno=11&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_11_content:
  string
  line `(1) It shall be the general duty of the Commission to advise the`
  line `Central Government in the matter of preserving, developing and maintaining the aesthetic quality of`
  line `urban and environmental design within Delhi and to provide advice and guidance to any local body in`
  line `respect of any project of building operations or engineering operations or any development proposal`
  line `which affects or is likely to affect the sky-line or the aesthetic quality of surroundings or any public`
  line `amenity provided therein.`
  line
  line `(2) Subject to the provisions of sub-section (1), it shall be the duty of the Commission to scrutinise,`
  line `approve, reject or modify proposals in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) development of district centres, civic centres, areas earmarked for Government administrative`
  line `buildings and for residential complexes, public parks and public gardens;`
  line
  line `(b) re-development of the area within the jurisdiction of New Delhi Municipal Committee`
  line `including Connaught Place Complex and its environs, Central Vista, the entire bungalow area of`
  line `Lutyen's New Delhi, and such other areas as the Central Government may, by notification in the`
  line `Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `(c) plans, architectural expressions and visual appearance of new buildings in the centres, areas,`
  line `parks and gardens specified in clauses (a) and (b) including selections of models for statues and`
  line `fountains therein;`
  line
  line `(d) re-development of areas in the vicinity of Jama Masjid, Red Fort, Qutab, Humayun's Tomb,`
  line `Old Fort, Tuglakabad and of such other places of historical importance as the Central Government`
  line `may, by notification in the Official Gazette, specify;`
  line
  line `(e) conservation, preservation and beautification of monumental buildings, public parks and`
  line `public gardens including location or installation of statues or fountains therein;`
  line
  line `(f) under passes, over-passes and regulations of street furniture and hoardings;`
  line
  line `(g) location and plans of power houses, water towers, television and other communication towers`
  line `and other allied structures;`
  line
  line `(h) any other projects or lay-out which is calculated to beautify Delhi or to add to its cultural`
  line `vitality or to enhance the quality of the surroundings thereof;`
  line
  line `(i) such other matters as may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `Explanation.--For the purposes of this sub-section,--`
  line
  line `(i) "civic centre" means the headquarters of a local body comprising therein its office buildings`
  line `and buildings intended for cultural activities;`
  line
  line `(ii) "Connaught Place Complex" means the area comprising Connaught Place and its extension`
  line `measuring approximately 140 hectares, being the area described as Zone D-I (Revised) in the Delhi`
  line `Master Plan;`
  line
  line `(iii) "district centre" means a self-contained unit created in the Delhi Master Plan comprising`
  line `areas for retail shopping, general business, commercial and professional offices, forwarding, booking`
  line `and Government offices, cinemas, restaurants and other places of entertainment.`
  line
  line `(3) Without prejudice to the provisions contained in sub-section (1) and sub-section (2), the`
  line `Commission may suo motu promote and secure the development, re-development or beautification of any`
  line `areas in Delhi in respect of which no proposals in that behalf have been received from any local body.`
obj_root_law_sections_11_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_12:
  sectionId (24108)
  sectionNo (12)
  orderNo 12
  title `Duty of local bodies to refer development proposals, etc., to the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_12_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24108&sectionno=12&orderno=12&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_12_content:
  string
  line `Notwithstanding anything contained in any other law for the time being in force, every local body shall,`
  line `before according approval in respect of any building operations, engineering operations or development`
  line `proposals referred to in sub-section (1) of section 11 or intended to be undertaken in any area or locality`
  line `specified in sub-section (2) of that section, refer the same to the Commission for scrutiny and the decision`
  line `of the Commission in respect thereof shall be binding on such local body.`
obj_root_law_sections_12_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_13:
  sectionId (24109)
  sectionNo (13)
  orderNo 13
  title `Appeal to the Central Government in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_13_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24109&sectionno=13&orderno=13&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_13_content:
  string
  line `If any local body is aggrieved by a`
  line `decision of the Commission in respect of any building operation, engineering operation or development`
  line `proposal intended to be undertaken or notified, as the case may be, by that local body and referred to the`
  line `Commission under section 12, the local body may, within sixty days from the date of such decision,`
  line `prefer an appeal to the Central Government, and the Central Government may pass such order thereon as`
  line `it deems fit.`
obj_root_law_sections_13_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_14:
  sectionId (24110)
  sectionNo (14)
  orderNo 14
  title `Power to revise decision in certain cases.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_14_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24110&sectionno=14&orderno=14&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_14_content:
  string
  line `Nothing contained in this Act shall preclude the`
  line `Central Government from calling for and examining, on its own motion, if it considers it necessary so to`
  line `do in the public interest, any case in which a decision has been made by the Commission under section 12`
  line `but no appeal lies thereto, and passing such order thereon as it thinks fit:`
  line
  line `Provided that no such order shall be made prejudicially affecting any person except after giving him`
  line `an opportunity of making a representation in the matter.`
obj_root_law_sections_14_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_15:
  sectionId (24111)
  sectionNo (15)
  orderNo 15
  title `Powers of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_15_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24111&sectionno=15&orderno=15&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_15_content:
  string
  line `for the purpose of performing its functions under this Act, the`
  line `Commission shall have the same powers as are vested in a civil court while trying a suit under the Code`
  line `of Civil Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908), in respect of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) summoning and enforcing the attendance of any person and examining him;`
  line
  line `(b) requiring discovery and production of any documents;`
  line
  line `(c) receiving evidence on affidavits;`
  line
  line `(d) requisitioning any public record or copies thereof from any office;`
  line
  line `(e) any other matter which may be prescribed by rules.`
obj_root_law_sections_15_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_16:
  sectionId (24112)
  sectionNo (16)
  orderNo 16
  title `Payment to the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_16_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24112&sectionno=16&orderno=16&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_16_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, after due appropriation made by`
  line `Parliament by law in this behalf, pay to the Commission in each financial year such sums as the Central`
  line `Government may consider necessary for the performance of the functions of the Commission under this`
  line Act.
obj_root_law_sections_16_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_17:
  sectionId (24113)
  sectionNo (17)
  orderNo 17
  title `Fund of the Commission.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_17_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24113&sectionno=17&orderno=17&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_17_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall have its own fund, and all sums which`
  line `may, from time to time, be paid to it by the Central Government shall be carried to the fund of the`
  line `Commission and all payments by the Commission shall be made therefrom.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission may spend such sums as it thinks fit for performing its functions under this Act,`
  line `and such sums shall be treated as expenditure payable out of the fund of the Commission.`
  line
  line `(3) All moneys in the fund shall be deposited in such bank or invested in such manner as may, subject`
  line `to the approval of the Central Government, be decided by the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_17_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_18:
  sectionId (24114)
  sectionNo (18)
  orderNo 18
  title Budget.
  content obj_root_law_sections_18_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24114&sectionno=18&orderno=18&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_18_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare, in such form and within such time, each year as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules, a budget in respect of the financial year next ensuing showing the estimated receipts`
  line `and expenditure, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government.`
obj_root_law_sections_18_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_19:
  sectionId (24115)
  sectionNo (19)
  orderNo 19
  title `Annual report.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_19_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24115&sectionno=19&orderno=19&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_19_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall prepare once every year, in such form and within such`
  line `time as may be prescribed by rules, an annual report giving a true and full account of its activities during`
  line `the previous year, and copies thereof shall be forwarded to the Central Government, and the Central`
  line `Government shall cause every such report to be laid before both Houses of Parliament.`
obj_root_law_sections_19_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_20:
  sectionId (24116)
  sectionNo (20)
  orderNo 20
  title `Accounts and audit.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_20_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24116&sectionno=20&orderno=20&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_20_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Commission shall cause to be maintained such books of accounts`
  line `and other books in relation to its accounts in such form and in such manner as may, in consultation with`
  line `the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(2) The Commission shall, as soon as may be after closing its annual accounts, prepare a statement of`
  line `accounts in such form as may be prescribed by rules, and forward the same to the Comptroller and`
  line `Auditor-General of India by such date, as the Central Government may, in consultation with the`
  line `Comptroller and Auditor-General of India, determine.`
  line
  line `(3) The accounts of the Commission shall be audited by the Comptroller and Auditor-General of India`
  line `at such times and in such manner as he thinks fit.`
  line
  line `(4) The annual accounts of the Commission together with the audit report thereon shall be forwarded`
  line `to the Central Government, and the Central Government shall cause the same to be laid before both`
  line `Houses of Parliament and shall also forward a copy of the audit report to the Commission for taking`
  line `appropriate action on the matters arising out of the audit report.`
obj_root_law_sections_20_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_21:
  sectionId (24117)
  sectionNo (21)
  orderNo 21
  title `Returns and information.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_21_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24117&sectionno=21&orderno=21&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_21_content:
  string
  line `The Commission shall furnish to the Central Government such`
  line `returns or other information with respect to its fund or activities as the Central Government may, from`
  line `time to time, require.`
obj_root_law_sections_21_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_22:
  sectionId (24118)
  sectionNo (22)
  orderNo 22
  title `Power to exempt.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_22_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24118&sectionno=22&orderno=22&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_22_content:
  string
  line `The Central Government may, subject to such conditions as may be`
  line `prescribed by rules in this behalf, exempt any building, building operation or engineering operation which`
  line `has been designed as a result of an architectural competition, from the operation of all or any of the`
  line `provisions of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_22_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_23:
  sectionId (24119)
  sectionNo (23)
  orderNo 23
  title `Delegation of powers.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_23_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24119&sectionno=23&orderno=23&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_23_content:
  string
  line `The Commission may, by general or special order in writing, delegate to`
  line `the Chairman or any other member or any officer of the Commission, subject to such conditions and`
  line `limitations, if any, as may be specified in the order, such of its powers and functions under this Act as it`
  line `may deem necessary for the efficient running of the day-to-day administration of the Commission.`
obj_root_law_sections_23_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_24:
  sectionId (24120)
  sectionNo (24)
  orderNo 24
  title `Members and officers of the Commission to be public servants.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_24_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24120&sectionno=24&orderno=24&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_24_content:
  string
  line `All members and officers of`
  line `the Commission shall, when acting or purporting to act in pursuance of any of the provisions of this Act,`
  line `be deemed to be public servants within the meaning of section 21 of the Indian Penal Code (45 of 1860).`
obj_root_law_sections_24_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_25:
  sectionId (24121)
  sectionNo (25)
  orderNo 25
  title `Protection of action taken in good faith.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_25_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24121&sectionno=25&orderno=25&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_25_content:
  string
  line `No suit or other legal proceeding shall lie against any`
  line `member or officer of the Commission in respect of anything which is in good faith done or intended to be`
  line `done in pursuance of this Act.`
obj_root_law_sections_25_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_26:
  sectionId (24122)
  sectionNo (26)
  orderNo 26
  title `Power to make rules.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_26_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24122&sectionno=26&orderno=26&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_26_content:
  string
  line `(1) The Central Government may, by notification in the Official Gazette,`
  line `make rules to carry out the purposes of this Act.`
  line
  line `(2) In particular, and without prejudice to the generality of the foregoing power, such rules may`
  line `provide for all or any of the following matters, namely:--`
  line
  line `(a) the salaries, if any, allowances and other terms and conditions of service of members of the`
  line Commission;
  line
  line `(b) the terms and conditions of service of the Secretary of the Commission;`
  line
  line `(c) the matters in respect of which the Commission may tender advice to the Central Government`
  line `under clause (i) of sub-section (2) of section 11;`
  line
  line `(d) the form in which, and the time within which, the budget and annual report of the`
  line `Commission may be prepared and forwarded to the Central Government;`
  line
  line `(e) the form and manner in which the accounts of the Commission may be maintained, and the`
  line `time at which, and the manner in which, such accounts may be audited;`
  line
  line `(f) the returns and information which the Commission may be required to furnish to the Central`
  line Government;
  line
  line `(g) the conditions subject to which any building, building operation or engineering operation,`
  line `designed as a result of an architectural competition, may be exempted;`
  line
  line `(h) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed by rules.`
  line
  line `(3) Every rule made by the Central Government under this Act shall be laid, as soon as may be after it`
  line `is made, before each House of Parliament while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may`
  line `be comprised in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session`
  line `immediately following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any`
  line `modification in the rule or both Houses agree that the rule should not be made, the rule shall thereafter`
  line `have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that any such`
  line `modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done under`
  line `that rule.`
obj_root_law_sections_26_footnotes:
  string
  line
obj_root_law_sections_27:
  sectionId (24123)
  sectionNo (27)
  orderNo 27
  title `Power to make regulations.`
  content obj_root_law_sections_27_content
  footnotes obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes
  query abv=CEN&statehandle=123456789/1362&actid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737&sectionId=24123&sectionno=27&orderno=27&orgactid=AC_CEN_17_19_00007_197401_1517807320737
obj_root_law_sections_27_content:
  string
  line ^1
  line `[(1)] The Commission may, with the previous approval of the`
  line `Central Government, by notification in the Official Gazette, make regulations consistent with this Act and`
  line `the rules made thereunder for--`
  line
  line `(a) regulating the meetings of the Commission and the procedure for conducting business thereat;`
  line
  line `(b) regulating the manner in which and the purposes for which persons may be associated with`
  line `the Commission under section 8:`
  line
  line `(c) determining the terms and conditions of service of persons appointed by the Commission`
  line `under sub-section (3) of section 9;`
  line
  line `(d) any other matter which has to be or may be prescribed by regulations.`
  line
  line ^2
  line `[(2) Every regulation made under this section shall be laid, as soon as may be after it is made, before`
  line `each House of Parliament, while it is in session, for a total period of thirty days which may be comprised`
  line `in one session or in two or more successive sessions, and if, before the expiry of the session immediately`
  line `following the session or the successive sessions aforesaid, both Houses agree in making any modification`
  line `in the regulation or both Houses agree that the regulation should not be made the regulation shall`
  line `thereafter have effect only in such modified form or be of no effect, as the case may be; so, however, that`
  line `any such modification or annulment shall be without prejudice to the validity of anything previously done`
  line `under that regulation.]`
obj_root_law_sections_27_footnotes:
  string
  line `1 Section 27 renumbered as sub-section (1) thereof by Act 4 of 1986, s. 2 and the Schedule (w.e.f.15-5-1986).`
  line
  line `2 Ins. by s. 2 and the Schedule, ibid. (w.e.f. 15-5-1986).`
obj_root_law_translations:
